1
00:00:43,060 --> 00:00:46,780
=Auspicious Nobles=

2
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:49,940
=Episode 4=

3
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:52,500
(Fight Back, Rice Ball)

4
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:56,070
Stop right there.

5
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:58,520
(My legs...)

6
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:00,600
(Hang in there.)

7
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:07,920
What can I do for you, Young Master?

8
00:01:08,790 --> 00:01:09,950
Take off your veil.

9
00:01:13,430 --> 00:01:14,350
They got away.

10
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:21,510
Help me!

11
00:01:21,710 --> 00:01:22,760
Kill him!

12
00:01:30,870 --> 00:01:31,870
Step aside now.

13
00:01:32,150 --> 00:01:33,920
I can at least leave your body intact.

14
00:01:34,590 --> 00:01:35,640
Enough talk.

15
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,400
Your Highness, are you alright?

16
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:50,430
From this day forward,

17
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:53,920
Wangshi Tower will be nothing
but a stray dog.

18
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:08,030
(I was planning to make
a fortune with Yuanzhao.)

19
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,430
(But now...)

20
00:02:09,470 --> 00:02:10,960
(That scheming has his eyes on me.)

21
00:02:11,470 --> 00:02:14,280
(And today happens to be payday
for this bunch of troublemakers.)

22
00:02:14,870 --> 00:02:16,840
(My pockets are emptier than my face.)

23
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,630
(How am I supposed to pay them?)

24
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:23,870
Silver.

25
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,590
My dear brothers,

26
00:02:38,150 --> 00:02:38,870
I know

27
00:02:39,430 --> 00:02:42,030
today is payday again.

28
00:02:42,870 --> 00:02:43,800
But

29
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:48,190
Wangshi Tower has just
been through a difficult time.

30
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:50,030
Cut the nonsense.

31
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:52,190
Just tell us if you've got our money.

32
00:02:53,630 --> 00:02:55,430
You dead bamboo, don't push your luck.

33
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:57,590
If you can't pay us,
are you going to kill me?

34
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,400
You're way too obsessed with money.

35
00:02:59,450 --> 00:03:01,790
You don't have any money, yet you
still expect us to work for free.

36
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,950
Who's being unreasonable now?

37
00:03:03,190 --> 00:03:04,030
Fine.

38
00:03:05,590 --> 00:03:07,190
Now I finally see your true colors.

39
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:09,190
Just wait.

40
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:11,710
I'll scrape together the money tonight,
even if I have to sell everything I own.

41
00:03:11,710 --> 00:03:13,910
Once you've all been paid,
we'll go our separate ways.

42
00:03:14,190 --> 00:03:15,590
You're fired.

43
00:03:15,590 --> 00:03:16,870
I fire you.

44
00:03:16,870 --> 00:03:17,910
You don't want me?

45
00:03:20,590 --> 00:03:21,470
Die!

46
00:03:22,150 --> 00:03:23,240
- Die!
- Die!

47
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:30,310
I told you when you hired me.

48
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:31,840
I only sign lifetime contracts.

49
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:34,030
There are only
three possible endings for us.

50
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,590
You pay me, I work.

51
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,080
You don't pay me,

52
00:03:38,590 --> 00:03:39,240
die.

53
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:40,800
You don't want me,

54
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:41,960
die.

55
00:03:42,870 --> 00:03:45,590
So you're just clinging to me now?

56
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,800
I brought back a bunch of grown babies.

57
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:50,280
I can't send them away.

58
00:03:50,660 --> 00:03:52,390
I still have to spend money
keeping them fed.

59
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,700
I'll give you one day to think it over.

60
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,830
Think carefully
about how you'll support us.

61
00:04:00,590 --> 00:04:02,030
You're actually pretty kind.

62
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,960
I won't need a day.

63
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,190
This is my latest invention.

64
00:04:13,310 --> 00:04:16,160
The Portable Golden Salted Egg Yolk
Rice Ball.

65
00:04:16,830 --> 00:04:18,120
Delicious and filling.

66
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,360
Easy to carry.

67
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,800
It's a must-have item
for roaming the martial world,

68
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:24,630
lying low, carrying out assassinations,
setting up stalls, and getting rich.

69
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:26,830
Once it's launched,

70
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,240
it will definitely
start a craze in the Capital.

71
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,510
We have the advantage of numbers here.

72
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,430
Starting tomorrow,

73
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,600
you'll lead the brothers

74
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,480
to the four city gates
in every direction.

75
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:36,430
One stall per person.

76
00:04:37,390 --> 00:04:38,800
In less than a month,

77
00:04:38,810 --> 00:04:40,880
we'll definitely earn enough
for the monthly wages.

78
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:42,830
We're assassins.

79
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,430
And you want us to sell rice balls?

80
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:48,680
You need to think bigger.

81
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:51,560
An ordinary rice ball is cheap.

82
00:04:52,070 --> 00:04:53,560
But ours is different.

83
00:04:54,630 --> 00:04:55,390
Inside,

84
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:58,270
we can add pickles, sausages,
spicy gluten, pork floss,

85
00:04:58,480 --> 00:04:59,950
and so on.

86
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:01,390
It's actually

87
00:05:01,390 --> 00:05:03,720
a deluxe supreme Chinese savory crepe.

88
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,160
Try it.

89
00:05:06,310 --> 00:05:08,240
I guarantee that once you've had it,

90
00:05:08,290 --> 00:05:09,630
you'll think about it every day.

91
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,430
This thing?

92
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:19,430
(Why does this rice ball)

93
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,720
(make me feel so happy?)

94
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,750
There really is something to this.

95
00:05:25,430 --> 00:05:27,680
We'd be fools not to set up this stall.

96
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:32,190
I think you just don't want
to miss out on the money.

97
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,390
(Heavens.)

98
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,360
(How did a financial genius like me)

99
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:49,750
(end up bringing assassins
to sell rice balls?)

100
00:05:50,430 --> 00:05:52,040
(Zheng Yuanhe,)

101
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:54,120
(this isn't over between us.)

102
00:05:56,020 --> 00:05:57,580
(Zhao Prince's Residence)

103
00:05:58,820 --> 00:06:00,660
(Elegance Fills the Garden)

104
00:06:02,270 --> 00:06:03,070
Your Highness.

105
00:06:03,310 --> 00:06:04,870
(Jiang Shuo, Zheng Yuanzhao's personal guard)
Wangshi Tower has indeed been abandoned.

106
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:06,120
I asked around.

107
00:06:06,310 --> 00:06:07,390
I found nothing.

108
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:10,270
I never even received my secret pouch.

109
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,120
Who's trying to destroy
my hundredfold fortune?

110
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,430
In a few days,

111
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:17,070
I'll give you a brilliant strategy.

112
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:20,270
It'll have merchants across the land
making money for us.

113
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:23,390
Shall I send more men to keep looking?

114
00:06:24,390 --> 00:06:25,160
Forget it.

115
00:06:26,110 --> 00:06:28,190
Do you even know
what the Tower Master looks like?

116
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:35,310
The woman who used to
manage the Li family's business.

117
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:35,910
What's her name?

118
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,510
Li... Li Qingqing.

119
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:39,000
Where is she now?

120
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,950
I heard she's
the Pan family's daughter-in-law.

121
00:06:44,420 --> 00:06:45,100
(Inspectorate)

122
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:46,560
Your Highness!

123
00:06:48,190 --> 00:06:49,870
I have something
to report, Your Highness.

124
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,790
I am the General of the Left Wuwei Guard's
Northern Expedition Cavalry.

125
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:58,750
From this day forward,
I pledge my loyalty to Your Highness.

126
00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:00,300
I humbly ask for Your Highness' favor.

127
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,310
Pan Yang.

128
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:12,190
At your service.

129
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,830
Do you know what kind
of people I hate the most?

130
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:17,430
Well...

131
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:18,800
Well...

132
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,070
I'm too foolish to know.

133
00:07:20,510 --> 00:07:21,190
First,

134
00:07:22,510 --> 00:07:24,950
those who don't know when to stop
and keep pestering me.

135
00:07:26,190 --> 00:07:27,000
Second,

136
00:07:28,190 --> 00:07:31,950
those who lack ability
yet think too highly of themselves.

137
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:33,480
I...

138
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:33,920
I...

139
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,190
I would never mean that.

140
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:38,390
I... I simply admire Your Highness.

141
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,200
I only wish to
lighten Your Highness' burden.

142
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:43,510
Do you think I don't know

143
00:07:43,510 --> 00:07:45,270
how Wangshi Tower

144
00:07:45,870 --> 00:07:47,000
beat you black and blue?

145
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,240
Lighten my burden?

146
00:07:51,510 --> 00:07:52,950
Do you think you're qualified?

147
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:06,070
What did the Crown Prince say?

148
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:07,390
I didn't even see his face

149
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,680
before I was thrown out.

150
00:08:11,310 --> 00:08:12,160
If that's the case,

151
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:13,630
why not serve the Second Prince?

152
00:08:14,270 --> 00:08:15,120
The Second Prince?

153
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:17,750
The Second Prince holds no real power.

154
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:20,190
How could he help advance my career?

155
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:23,040
Yang, you're mistaken.

156
00:08:23,310 --> 00:08:25,310
The Second Prince
oversees the imperial merchants.

157
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:26,890
He has earned Great Yong immense wealth.

158
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:28,510
He is greatly favored by His Majesty.

159
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:31,160
Everyone in the imperial court is saying

160
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,670
His Majesty may...

161
00:08:39,630 --> 00:08:41,870
But I know nothing about business.

162
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,510
Do you have a good idea, my dear?

163
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,600
Don't worry, my dear.

164
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:50,030
I've heard Qingqing has built up
quite a business over the years.

165
00:08:50,390 --> 00:08:53,150
If we can persuade Qingqing
to transfer her business to us,

166
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:56,510
then present it to the Second Prince
under your name,

167
00:08:56,660 --> 00:08:58,440
why worry about
not getting an opportunity?

168
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:00,600
Muyan.

169
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:02,030
You truly are...

170
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:03,960
Miss.

171
00:09:05,790 --> 00:09:06,600
What is it?

172
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,120
Miss, I saw...

173
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,910
A man climbing over Qingqing's wall?

174
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,720
Did you see him clearly?

175
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:34,600
(Yuanzhao?)

176
00:09:37,260 --> 00:09:38,000
It looked like her.

177
00:09:39,310 --> 00:09:41,120
(That fool is trying
to uncover my identity.)

178
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,320
Tower Master?

179
00:10:00,030 --> 00:10:00,750
It's me,

180
00:10:01,030 --> 00:10:01,720
Yuanzhao.

181
00:10:03,630 --> 00:10:06,080
Who are you?

182
00:10:07,030 --> 00:10:08,180
(Could it really not be her?)

183
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,720
Adulterers!

184
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:15,590
Let's see where you think you're going!

185
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,080
Qingqing.

186
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,840
Even if you've been wronged,

187
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,390
you mustn't have
an affair with another man.

188
00:10:26,390 --> 00:10:29,080
What will become of the Pan
and Li families' reputation?

189
00:10:29,510 --> 00:10:31,480
So it was you.

190
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:36,000
No wonder when I questioned you politely
at Wangshi Tower the other day,

191
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,360
you deliberately humiliated me.

192
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:40,200
So you've been cheating on me all along.

193
00:10:40,510 --> 00:10:41,080
And you.

194
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:41,840
Me?

195
00:10:42,150 --> 00:10:44,240
While I was away defending our country,

196
00:10:44,390 --> 00:10:47,270
you were secretly meeting another man.

197
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:48,200
Shameless.

198
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,840
Don't go making false accusations.

199
00:10:53,390 --> 00:10:54,670
I don't even know this guy.

200
00:10:55,510 --> 00:10:56,480
If you ask me,

201
00:10:56,910 --> 00:10:58,200
he's here to steal.

202
00:11:01,030 --> 00:11:01,790
Me?

203
00:11:02,030 --> 00:11:03,000
Steal?

204
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:04,480
How dare you!

205
00:11:05,510 --> 00:11:07,240
Do you even know who you're talking to?

206
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:09,550
Caught red-handed,
and you're still denying it?

207
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:10,480
Men!

208
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,440
Tie these adulterers up.

209
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:13,620
Throw them into a pig cage!

210
00:11:13,630 --> 00:11:14,200
- Yes!
- Yes!

211
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:17,000
Who dares!

212
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:23,790
I already told you, he's a thief.

213
00:11:24,630 --> 00:11:27,630
General Pan has served in
the Northern Expedition Cavalry for over a year.

214
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:31,200
Surely you know
a few interrogation methods.

215
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,480
Why not interrogate him and find out?

216
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,120
Fine.

217
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:39,320
Then let's see whether your lover

218
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:41,750
can withstand my methods.

219
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,200
Insolence!

220
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:47,150
I am the Second Prince of Great Yong.

221
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:48,870
Let's see who's foolish enough
to lay a hand on me.

222
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:52,550
You...

223
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:53,910
Jerk!

224
00:11:58,480 --> 00:11:59,120
That's all?

225
00:11:59,550 --> 00:12:00,870
The Second Prince?

226
00:12:03,270 --> 00:12:04,870
This must be your token of love.

227
00:12:07,090 --> 00:12:07,670
Take him away!

228
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:08,440
- Yes!
- Yes!

229
00:12:18,630 --> 00:12:21,080
(That fool Yuanzhao was trying
to uncover my identity.)

230
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:22,670
(Serves him right.)

231
00:12:23,030 --> 00:12:24,280
(This is the perfect chance
to teach Pan Yang a lesson.)

232
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:25,690
(He actually
dared lay a hand on a prince.)

233
00:12:25,910 --> 00:12:27,360
(He's asking for a beating.)

234
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:30,720
Yang.

235
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:32,550
Qingqing, she...

236
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,670
Why are you still standing there?

237
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:35,750
Take her away!

238
00:12:36,270 --> 00:12:37,510
I'll walk myself.

239
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:47,530
♪Snowflakes settle gently
upon your brows♪

240
00:12:48,290 --> 00:12:51,670
♪Your dark hair
brushes across my fingertips♪

241
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:54,180
♪Your smile♪

242
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:56,730
♪Melts away the winter snow♪

243
00:12:56,730 --> 00:13:00,410
♪One fleeting glance says more
than a thousand words♪

244
00:13:00,870 --> 00:13:04,180
♪Yet I stand before you♪

245
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:08,750
♪Unable to recognize your eyes♪

246
00:13:09,170 --> 00:13:11,090
♪Though fate tries♪

247
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:13,670
♪To make us pass each other by♪

248
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:17,310
♪I choose to make our story whole♪

249
00:13:17,570 --> 00:13:19,200
♪Though time slips by♪

250
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,960
♪As day turns into night♪

251
00:13:21,480 --> 00:13:25,500
♪I still remember
our days at Wangshi Tower♪

252
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:28,300
♪One glance at you lasts a lifetime♪

253
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:30,090
♪Blessed by fate♪

254
00:13:30,090 --> 00:13:35,250
♪I believe this moment
will last forever♪

255
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:37,690
♪Your smiling face♪

256
00:13:37,690 --> 00:13:40,530
♪Is the most beautiful poem♪

257
00:13:40,530 --> 00:13:44,150
♪I'd rather spend my days with you♪

258
00:13:44,670 --> 00:13:48,130
♪And wander the world together♪

259
00:13:48,130 --> 00:13:49,470
♪Holding you close♪

260
00:13:49,470 --> 00:13:52,010
♪Envying neither lovers nor immortals♪

261
00:13:52,010 --> 00:13:54,330
♪Your tenderness♪

262
00:13:54,330 --> 00:13:57,190
♪Is the brightest moon♪

263
00:13:57,190 --> 00:14:00,890
♪I'd rather
pledge three lifetimes to you♪

264
00:14:01,410 --> 00:14:04,700
♪Our love will never fade away♪

265
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:07,160
♪Though heaven and earth grow old♪

266
00:14:07,690 --> 00:14:11,940
♪My heart will remain forever pure♪

267
00:14:21,420 --> 00:14:23,580
♪Your smiling face♪

268
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:26,370
♪Is the most beautiful poem♪

269
00:14:26,660 --> 00:14:30,530
♪I'd rather spend my days with you♪

270
00:14:30,740 --> 00:14:34,250
♪And wander the world together♪

271
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:35,570
♪Holding you close♪

272
00:14:35,570 --> 00:14:38,200
♪Envying neither lovers nor immortals♪

273
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:40,460
♪Your tenderness♪

274
00:14:40,460 --> 00:14:43,330
♪Is the brightest moon♪

275
00:14:43,330 --> 00:14:47,070
♪I'd rather
